[{"text": "I'm a filmmaker.", "start": 15.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "For the last 8 years,", "start": 17.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I have dedicated my life", "start": 19.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to documenting the work", "start": 21.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of Israelis and Palestinians", "start": 23.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who are trying to end the conflict", "start": 25.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "using peaceful means.", "start": 27.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "When I travel with my work", "start": 29.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "across Europe and the United States,", "start": 31.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "one question always comes up:", "start": 33.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Where is the Palestinian Gandhi?", "start": 38.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Why aren't Palestinians", "start": 40.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "using nonviolent resistance?", "start": 42.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The challenge I face when I hear this question", "start": 45.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is that often I have just returned from the Middle East", "start": 48.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "where I spent my time", "start": 51.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "filming dozens of Palestinians", "start": 53.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who are using nonviolence", "start": 55.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to defend their lands", "start": 57.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and water resources", "start": 59.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from Israeli soldiers and settlers.", "start": 61.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "These leaders are trying to forge", "start": 64.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a massive national nonviolent movement", "start": 67.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to end the occupation", "start": 70.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and build peace in the region.", "start": 72.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Yet, most of you", "start": 74.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have probably never heard about them.", "start": 76.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This divide between what's happening on the ground", "start": 79.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and perceptions abroad", "start": 81.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is one of the key reasons", "start": 83.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "why we don't have yet", "start": 85.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a Palestinian peaceful resistance movement", "start": 87.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that has been successful.", "start": 90.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So I'm here today", "start": 93.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to talk about the power of attention,", "start": 95.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the power of your attention,", "start": 97.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the emergence and development", "start": 100.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of nonviolent movements", "start": 102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the West Bank, Gaza and elsewhere --", "start": 104.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but today, my case study is going to be Palestine.", "start": 107.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I believe that what's mostly missing", "start": 111.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for nonviolence to grow", "start": 113.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is not for Palestinians", "start": 115.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to start adopting nonviolence,", "start": 117.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but for us to start paying attention", "start": 120.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to those who already are.", "start": 123.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Allow me to illustrate this point", "start": 127.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by taking you to this village", "start": 129.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "called Budrus.", "start": 131.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "About seven years ago,", "start": 133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they faced extinction,", "start": 135.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because Israel announced it would build a separation barrier,", "start": 137.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and part of this barrier", "start": 139.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "would be built on top of the village.", "start": 141.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They would lose 40 percent of their land", "start": 143.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and be surrounded,", "start": 145.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so they would lose free access", "start": 147.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the rest of the West Bank.", "start": 149.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Through inspired local leadership,", "start": 151.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they launched a peaceful resistance campaign", "start": 153.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to stop that from happening.", "start": 156.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Let me show you some brief clips,", "start": 158.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so you have a sense", "start": 160.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for what that actually looked like on the ground.", "start": 162.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Music)", "start": 165.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Palestinian Woman: We were told the wall", "start": 171.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "would separate Palestine from Israel.", "start": 174.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Here in Budrus,", "start": 177.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we realized the wall would steal our land.", "start": 179.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Israeli Man: The fence has, in fact,", "start": 181.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "created a solution to terror.", "start": 183.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Man: Today you're invited", "start": 186.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to a peaceful march.", "start": 189.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "You are joined", "start": 195.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by dozens of your Israeli brothers and sisters.", "start": 198.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Israeli Activist: Nothing scares the army", "start": 200.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "more than nonviolent opposition.", "start": 203.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Woman: We saw the men", "start": 208.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "trying to push the soldiers,", "start": 210.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but none of them could do that.", "start": 212.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But I think the girls could do it.", "start": 215.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Fatah Party Member: We must empty our minds", "start": 222.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of traditional thinking.", "start": 225.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Hamas Party Member: We were in complete harmony,", "start": 230.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and we wanted to spread it to all of Palestine.", "start": 233.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Chanting: One united nation.", "start": 236.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Fatah, Hamas and the Popular Front!", "start": 238.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "News Anchor: The clashes over the fence continue.", "start": 242.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Reporter: Israeli border police were sent to disperse the crowd.", "start": 244.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "They were allowed to use any force necessary.", "start": 248.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Gunshots)", "start": 250.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Man: These are live bullets.", "start": 252.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's like Fallujah. Shooting everywhere.", "start": 254.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Israeli Activist: I was sure we were all going to die.", "start": 257.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But there were others around me who weren't even cowering.", "start": 260.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Israeli Soldier: A nonviolent protest", "start": 268.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is not going to stop the [unclear].", "start": 270.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Protester: This is a peaceful march.", "start": 273.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There is no need to use violence.", "start": 275.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Chanting: We can do it! We can do it!", "start": 278.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "We can do it!", "start": 282.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Julia Bacha: When I first heard", "start": 286.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the story of Budrus,", "start": 288.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I was surprised", "start": 290.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the international media had failed to cover", "start": 292.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the extraordinary set of events", "start": 295.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that happened seven years ago,", "start": 297.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in 2003.", "start": 299.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What was even more surprising", "start": 301.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was the fact that Budrus was successful.", "start": 303.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The residents, after 10 months of peaceful resistance,", "start": 306.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "convinced the Israeli government", "start": 309.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to move the route of the barrier off their lands", "start": 312.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and to the green line,", "start": 315.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which is the internationally recognized boundary", "start": 317.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "between Israel and the Palestinian Territories.", "start": 320.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The resistance in Budrus", "start": 323.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has since spread", "start": 325.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to villages across the West Bank", "start": 327.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and to Palestinian neighborhoods in Jerusalem.", "start": 329.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Yet the media remains mostly silent", "start": 333.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on these stories.", "start": 336.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This silence carries profound consequences", "start": 339.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for the likelihood", "start": 342.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that nonviolence can grow,", "start": 344.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or even survive,", "start": 346.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Palestine.", "start": 348.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Violent resistance", "start": 350.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and nonviolent resistance", "start": 352.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "share one very important thing in common;", "start": 354.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "they are both a form of theater", "start": 358.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "seeking an audience to their cause.", "start": 361.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If violent actors", "start": 364.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are the only ones constantly getting front-page covers", "start": 366.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and attracting international attention", "start": 369.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the Palestinian issue,", "start": 371.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it becomes very hard", "start": 373.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for nonviolent leaders", "start": 375.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to make the case to their communities", "start": 377.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that civil disobedience", "start": 379.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a viable option", "start": 381.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in addressing their plight.", "start": 383.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The power of attention", "start": 385.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is probably going to come as no surprise", "start": 387.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the parents in the room.", "start": 389.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The surest way", "start": 392.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to make your child throw increasingly louder tantrums", "start": 394.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is by giving him attention", "start": 397.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the first time he throws a fit.", "start": 399.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The tantrum will become", "start": 401.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what childhood psychologists call", "start": 403.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a functional behavior,", "start": 405.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "since the child has learned", "start": 407.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that he can get parental attention out of it.", "start": 409.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Parents can incentivize or disincentivize behavior", "start": 413.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "simply by giving or withdrawing", "start": 417.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "attention to their children.", "start": 419.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But that's true for adults too.", "start": 422.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In fact, the behavior", "start": 425.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of entire communities and countries", "start": 427.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "can be influenced,", "start": 429.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "depending on where", "start": 431.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the international community chooses", "start": 433.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to focus its attention.", "start": 435.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I believe that at the core of ending the conflict in the Middle East", "start": 438.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and bringing peace", "start": 442.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is for us", "start": 444.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to transform nonviolence", "start": 446.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into a functional behavior", "start": 448.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by giving a lot more attention", "start": 450.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the nonviolent leaders on the ground today.", "start": 452.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In the course of taking my film to villages", "start": 456.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the West Bank, in Gaza and in East Jerusalem,", "start": 459.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I have seen the impact", "start": 462.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that even one documentary film can have", "start": 464.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in influencing the transformation.", "start": 467.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "In a village called Wallajeh,", "start": 471.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which sits very close to Jerusalem,", "start": 473.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the community was facing", "start": 476.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a very similar plight to Budrus.", "start": 478.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They were going to be surrounded, lose a lot of their lands", "start": 480.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and not have freedom of access,", "start": 483.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "either to the West Bank or Jerusalem.", "start": 485.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They had been using nonviolence for about two years", "start": 488.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but had grown disenchanted", "start": 491.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "since nobody was paying attention.", "start": 493.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So we organized a screening.", "start": 496.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "A week later,", "start": 499.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they held the most well-attended", "start": 501.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and disciplined", "start": 503.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "demonstration to date.", "start": 505.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The organizers say", "start": 508.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the villagers, upon seeing the story of Budrus", "start": 510.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "documented in a film,", "start": 512.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "felt that there were indeed people", "start": 514.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "following what they were doing,", "start": 516.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that people cared.", "start": 518.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So they kept on going.", "start": 520.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "On the Israeli side,", "start": 522.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there is a new peace movement called Solidariot,", "start": 524.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "which means solidarity in Hebrew.", "start": 527.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The leaders of this movement have been using Budrus", "start": 530.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as one of their primary recruiting tools.", "start": 533.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They report", "start": 536.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that Israelis who had never been active before,", "start": 538.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "upon seeing the film,", "start": 540.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "understand the power of nonviolence", "start": 542.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and start joining their activities.", "start": 544.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The examples of Wallajeh", "start": 546.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the Solidariot movement", "start": 548.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "show that even a small-budget independent film", "start": 550.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "can play a role", "start": 554.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in transforming nonviolence", "start": 556.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into a functional behavior.", "start": 558.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now imagine the power", "start": 561.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that big media players could have", "start": 563.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "if they started covering", "start": 566.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the weekly nonviolent demonstrations", "start": 568.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "happening in villages", "start": 570.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "like Bil'in, Ni'lin,", "start": 572.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Wallajeh,", "start": 574.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Jerusalem neighborhoods", "start": 576.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "like Sheikh Jarrah and Silwan --", "start": 578.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the nonviolent leaders", "start": 581.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "would become more visible,", "start": 583.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "valued and effective", "start": 585.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in their work.", "start": 587.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I believe", "start": 590.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the most important thing", "start": 592.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is to understand", "start": 594.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that if we don't pay attention to these efforts,", "start": 596.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they are invisible,", "start": 599.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it's as if they never happened.", "start": 601.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But I have seen first hand", "start": 603.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that if we do,", "start": 605.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they will multiply.", "start": 607.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If they multiply,", "start": 609.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "their influence will grow", "start": 611.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the overall Israeli-Palestinian conflict.", "start": 613.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And theirs is the kind of influence", "start": 615.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that can finally", "start": 618.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "unblock the situation.", "start": 620.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "These leaders have proven that nonviolence works", "start": 622.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in places like Budrus.", "start": 625.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Let's give them attention", "start": 627.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so they can prove it works everywhere.", "start": 629.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 632.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 634.26, "duration": 11.0}]